it.slyce.sdk

Interface SlyceSession


  • public interface SlyceSession
    Defines the behavior of a Slyce SDK session. Specifically, the session is used to create and manage Slyce SDK operations (e.g., barcode detection, image match, and visual search).

      • createScanner

        SlyceScanner createScanner(android.content.Context context,
                           android.hardware.Camera camera,
                           java.lang.String lensId)
                    throws SlyceInvalidSessionException,
                           SlyceError
        Creates a new SlyceScanner matching the spec of the provided lens ID. Note that if the SlyceSession has been closed or the lens ID is not found, null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        camera - The camera.
        context - The context.
        lensId - The lens ID used to configure the SlyceScanner.
        Returns:
        a new SlyceScanner, or null if lens ID not found or session is closed.
        Throws:
        SlyceInvalidSessionException
        SlyceError

      • buildSearchTask

        @Deprecated
SlyceSearchTask buildSearchTask(SlyceSearchRequest request,
                                            java.lang.String workflowId)
        Deprecated. as of Slyce SDK v5.1.0, replaced by startSearchTask(SlyceSearchRequest, String, SlyceSearchTaskListener)
        Builds a SlyceSearchTask based on the provided request and workflow ID. Note that if the session has been closed or the workflow ID is not found, null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        request - The search task request.
        workflowId - The ID of the workflow to use.
        Returns:
        a new SlyceSearchTask for the request and workflow ID, or null if workflow ID is not found or session is closed.
